   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,033:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Adding a New Training Model
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,051:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This guide explains how to add a new model to the connectome-gnn training pipeline. The codebase uses a registry
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,056:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: pattern: you write a model class, register it under a name, and create a YAML config referencing that name. The
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,058:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: trainer picks it up automatically.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,059:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Architecture Overview
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,060:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The pipeline has three layers. The 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,061:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: config
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,063:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,065:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: config/{biomodel}/{name}.yaml
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,067:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ) defines the dataset and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,068:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: model name. The 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,069:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: registry
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,070:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,072:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: src/connectome_gnn/models/registry.py:42
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,073:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ) maps 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,075:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: signal_model_name
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,076:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  strings to model classes. The 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,077:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: trainer
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,078:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,080:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: src/connectome_gnn/models/graph_trainer.py:84-91
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,082:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ) dispatches to the right training loop based
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,082:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: on the model name.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,085:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Two training loops exist. 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,086:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: data_train_gnn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,087:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (line 96) handles GNN and Linear ODE models that take 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,088:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (NeuronState, edge_index)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,090:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  as input. 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,091:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: data_train_gnn_RNN
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,102:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (line 853) handles sequential models
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,104:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (RNN, LSTM) that take a packed state tensor and maintain hidden state across time steps. The dispatcher at line 86
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,105:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: checks if 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,107:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 'rnn'
