   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,362:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  to an existing dataset name like 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,364:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: drosophila_cx
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,366:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  and the trainer will load the pre-generated data. If you use a new dataset name (e.g. 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,367:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: drosophila_cx_mymodel
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,369:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ), data generation will create a new folder under 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,370:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: graphs_data/
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,372:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: .
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,373:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The routing function 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,374:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: add_pre_folder
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,376:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  in 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,378:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: src/connectome_gnn/utils.py:314
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,381:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  maps dataset names to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,383:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: config directories using prefix matching. Any dataset starting with 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,384:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: drosophila_cx
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,385:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  routes to 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,387:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: config/drosophila_cx/
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,388:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: . Same for 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,389:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: larva
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,391:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  and 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,392:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: zebrafish_oculomotor
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,394:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: .
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,395:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Step 4: Training
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,397:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: If your model is a GNN-style model (not RNN), the trainer at 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,398:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: graph_trainer.py:527
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,399:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  calls:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,402:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: pred, in_features, msg = model(batched_state, batched_edges,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,403:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: data_id=data_id, return_all=True)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,404:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: If it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,405:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,406:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s an RNN-style model, the trainer at 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,408:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: graph_trainer.py:902
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,409:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  calls:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,411:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: pred, h = model(x, h=h, return_all=True)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,412:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: To route your model to the RNN loop, include 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,413:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 'rnn'
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,414:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  or 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,416:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 'lstm'
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,417:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  in the signal
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,418:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,420:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: model
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,421:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,423:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: name. Otherwise it goes
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,423:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: through the GNN loop.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,425:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Run training with:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,427:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: python GNN_train.py -o generate_train_test_plot
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,428:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: drosophila_cx_mymodel
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,429:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Or through the LLM exploration pipeline:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,432:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: python GNN_LLM.py -o generate_train_test_plot_Claude
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,433:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: drosophila_cx_mymodel iterations=128 --cluster
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,434:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Step 5: Analysis and Plotting
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,436:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: GNN_PlotFigure.py
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,437:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  handles all post-training analysis. It extracts 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,438:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: model.W
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,439:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  to compute 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,441:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: connectivity_R2
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,442:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,443:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: against ground truth, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,445:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: model.a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,446:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  for clustering, and runs rollout prediction. The analysis code checks 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,447:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: signal_model_name
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,449:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  for routing at several points (lines 661, 666, 740) — if your model name contains 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,460:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 'linear'
   DEBUG: 2026-03-24 06:54:43,461:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , 
